<h1>На подступах к общеевропейской науке?</h1>
<h2>Денн М. , Гоготишвили Л.А. </h2>
<p><span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: 'Garamond','serif'; font-size: 12pt"><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font><strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 11pt">Аннотация: </span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 11pt">На основе работы совместной французско-русской исследовательской группы &laquo;<em>Русская и западноевропейская культуры: дифференциальные и интегральные аспекты</em>&raquo; (2010-2015) описаны условия достижения общеевропейской науки и общеевропейской гуманитарной эпистемологии, отмечены препятствия на пути к достижению этой задачи</span><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 11pt">.</span><span style="font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'"> </span><font face="Times New Roman"><br /></font></span></p><p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 14pt" align="left"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 11pt">Ключевые слова: </span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 11pt">Общеевропейский контекст, глобализация и специфические культуры, личностное и родовое, степени и формы универсализации культуры, интернаука, общеевропейская гуманитарная эпистемология.</span></p><p><font face="Times New Roman"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 18pt">Towards a Common European science? </span></strong></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font><span style="background: lightgrey; font-family: 'Georgia','serif'"><font style="background-color: #ffffff"><strong><font style="background-color: #e1e1e1">Maryse Dennes</font> (Professeur des Universit</strong><span style="background-position: 0% 0%; font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 12pt; background-image: none; background-attachment: scroll; background-repeat: repeat; background-size: auto; background-origin: padding-box; background-clip: border-box"><strong>&eacute;s,</strong></span><strong>&nbsp;Universit&eacute; Bordeaux Montaigne, CEMMC)</strong></font></span><font face="Times New Roman"><br /><strong><span style="background: lightgrey; font-family: 'Georgia','serif'"><font style="background-color: #ffffff">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font style="background-color: #e1e1e1">Liudmila Gogotishvili</font> (Institute of Philosophy RAS)</font></span></strong></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman">  </font><strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'">&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 11pt">Abstract:</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 11pt">&nbsp; On the basis of work executed by the mutual French-Russian group &ldquo;Russian and West-European cultures: integral and differential aspects&rdquo; (2010-2015) the paper describes the conditions, on which a Common European science and humanitarian epistemology may be created, as well as obstacles on the path..</span></p><p><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp; </font><strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 11pt">Keywords:</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Georgia','serif'; font-size: 11pt"> common European context, globalization and specific cultures, personal and generic, degrees and forms of universalization in culture, inter-science, common European humanitarian epistemology</span></p><p>&nbsp;<font face="Times New Roman"> <strong>DOI: 10.24411/2077-6608-2015-00004</strong></font></p>	<p class="fullTextLink">
		<a href="https://vox-journal.org/content/Vox19/Vox19-GogotishviliDenn.pdf">Полный текст RU</a>
	</p>
